    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Now, let's get started!</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a little drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Chop your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong> in half (use scissors for speed!)</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>halved bacon</strong> to the pan and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until golden and crisp</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the bacon is cooking, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Heat a large, wide-based pot with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and cook for 1 min or until fragrant</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>baked beans </strong>to the pot with your <strong>ground</strong> <strong>smoked paprika</strong>, <strong>BBQ sauce</strong>,<strong> pomegranate molasses </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat and once boiling, reduce the heat to medium</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the bacon is golden and crisp, add it to the pot and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Cook for 3-4 min further or until the sauce has thickened \u2013 these are your <strong>bacon & smoky Boston-style beans</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>ciabatta[s]</strong> in half and place in the <strong>toaster</strong> for 1-2 min or until toasted</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop your <strong>chives</strong> finely</p><p>Combine the <strong>soured cream</strong> and <strong>chopped chives</strong> in a small bowl with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp] </span><strong>cold water</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> soured cream & chive sauce</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>lettuce</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Cut the<strong> lettuce</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/bacon-and-smoky-boston-style-beans-with-soured-cream-and-chives/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>bacon & smoky Boston-style beans </strong>with the <strong>toasted ciabatta</strong> and <strong>lettuce wedges </strong>to the side</p><p>Drizzle the <strong>soured cream & chive sauce </strong>over everything</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
